				\begin{document}$$I{C}^{\ast }(t)=-\,\mathrm{log}(p(k,n|t))+IC(t)$$\end{document}IC⁎(t)=−log(p(k,n|t))+IC(t)where IC (t) is computed from the prior knowledge by annotations of corpus or by the expert knowledge embedded in the DAG. Note that by including {n, k} in the IC of term, IC* (t) accounts for the enrichment of the term by querying gene set.

